sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as RHOAI Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    participant KServe as KServe Service<br/>(ClusterIP)
    participant VllmHTTP as vllm-spyre HTTP<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant VllmGRPC as vllm-spyre gRPC<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant Spyre as IBM Spyre<br/>Accelerator (PCIe)
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>S3/PVC
    participant HF as Hugging Face Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over VllmHTTP,S3: Flow 0: Container Startup - Model Loading
    VllmHTTP->>S3: Load model weights<br/>HTTPS/443 (S3) or Volume (PVC)<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS IAM
    S3-->>VllmHTTP: Model artifacts
    VllmHTTP->>HF: Download tokenizer config (optional)<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+ / Bearer Token
    HF-->>VllmHTTP: Tokenizer files
    VllmHTTP->>Spyre: Initialize model on accelerator<br/>PCIe/device driver

    Note over Client,Spyre: Flow 1: OpenAI-Compatible Inference Request
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (platform-managed)
    Gateway->>KServe: Forward request<br/>Platform-managed routing
    KServe->>VllmHTTP: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/8000 (pod-internal)
    VllmHTTP->>Spyre: Inference computation<br/>PCIe/device driver
    Spyre-->>VllmHTTP: Generated tokens
    VllmHTTP-->>KServe: JSON response<br/>(completion result)
    KServe-->>Gateway: Forward response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS response<br/>TLS 1.3

    Note over KServe,Spyre: Flow 2: TGIS gRPC Inference Request
    KServe->>VllmGRPC: GenerationService RPC<br/>gRPC/8033 (pod-internal)
    VllmGRPC->>Spyre: Inference computation<br/>PCIe/device driver
    Spyre-->>VllmGRPC: Generated tokens
    VllmGRPC-->>KServe: gRPC response<br/>(generation result)
